CommonFields.Title: PMMA–titania nanocomposites: Properties and thermal degradation behaviour
Author: Motaung, Tshwafo Elias
Luyt, Adriaan Stephanus
Bondioli, Federica
Messori, Massimo
Saladino, Maria Luisa
Spinella, Alberto
Nasillo, Giorgio
Caponetti, Eugenio
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, University of the Free State (Qwaqwa Campus), Private Bag X13, Phuthaditjhaba 9866, South Africa

Mixing.Description: glycine:titanyl nitrate molar ratio = 2 and glycine:NH4NO3 molar ratio = 0.5

Heating.Description: in an oven until complete dehydration
divide in two parts and thermally treated in air to crystalize the anatase

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: performed from 40 to 180 C in the bending mode at a heating rate of 5 C min1 and a frequency of 1 Hz

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: equipped with a Cu tube and a scintillation detector beam

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The analyses were done under flowing nitrogen at a constant flow rate of 20 mL min1. Samples (5e10 mg) were heated from 25 to 600 C at heating rates of 3, 5, 7 and 9 C min1.

Nuclear_Magnetic_Resonance.Equipment: Bruker Avance II 400 MHz (9.4 T) spectrometer
Nuclear_Magnetic_Resonance.Description: operating at 100.63 MHz for the 13C nucleus with an MAS rate of 10 kHz, 400 scans, a contact time of 1.5 s and a repetition delay of 2 s
